    <string name="how_to_use">How to use</string>
    <string name="tutorial_title">How to use Grammar Float</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step1_title">1. Normal Mode (Context Menu)</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step1_desc">Select any text you are typing and look for the \'Check Grammar\' option in the copy/paste menu. This works in many apps but may be restricted by some.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step2_title">2. Seamless Mode (Accessibility)</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step2_desc">Once enabled, a small floating button will automatically appear on the screen whenever you are typing. Tap it to instantly fix your grammar without having to manually select the text!</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step3_title">3. API Key Required</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step3_desc">To power the AI, you must add an API key from Anthropic, OpenAI, or Google Gemini in the settings below.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step4_title">4. Custom Models (Optional)</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step4_desc">You can enter a model ID provided by the selected provider in the settings. To reset to the default model, simply clear the model text field and tap Verify again.</string>
